<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture,Products.Mimic" MadCap:lastBlockDepth="2" MadCap:lastHeight="101" MadCap:lastWidth="505">
    <body>
        <p>You can add a zoom effect to an object in<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText>. This creates a 3D effect that magnifies (and therefore emphasizes) a specific area in<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> an image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> a frame</MadCap:conditionalText> so that it appears closer than the rest of the<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture"> image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic"> frame</MadCap:conditionalText>. When you create a zoom effect, you have control over the appearance of the effect, including the position of the enlarged area and the percentage at which the area is magnified.</p>
    </body>
